OL,5, There is a tiny special club, a        
OL,6, powerful group who knew Queen Elizabeth
OL,7, in a particular and private way - her  
OL,8, prime ministers.                       
OL,10,FThey all used to speak to her in person
OL,11,Ffor an hour or so each week. The       
OL,12,Fmonarch was their confidant of sorts,  
OL,13,Fan adviser providing a shrewd ear.     
OL,15,FFor this week's programme I've been    
OL,16,Fspeaking to Gordon Brown, David Cameron
OL,17,Fand Theresa May, the Queen's 11th,     
OL,18,F12th, and 13th prime ministers, about  
OL,19,Fwhy it matters, their memories of one  
OL,20,Fmonarch, and their hopes for the next. 
